<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-2885BF56-7B36-423E-B567-AB29516FD4CC" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-2885BF56-7B36-423E-B567-AB29516FD4CC" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">19 How to remove the take-up media shaft</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-0E3E2CA2-5349-4FAF-80F5-347AA9765351"><p class="- topic/p ">This document describes how to remove the take-up media shaft. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-F8EE43B1-36AF-4F86-8810-3B686A03AF19" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_871F5A47506844048EAA4DAB5828784E" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_21C8B271522344C0958B457D5D3BA087" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">If there is media on the take-up media shaft, make sure the media is cut and out of the system.
</p></li></ul></prereq><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph ">Attention:</ph></title><p class="- topic/p ">If there is a lot of media on the take-up media shaft, 2 people are required to lift and remove it.
</p></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-1C6A5506-8461-4BFD-8B7C-FB47C7EF289A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2F9C8379-6D32-440A-9A0D-A69A6043427B-low.png" id="IMAGE_1EE8E6CF131C4064913FA3D3B4E13E44" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2F9C8379-6D32-440A-9A0D-A69A6043427B-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_521D99F65A144454BCCB5E25B2366263" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_F0323E51D9184ACDAA5DAB8F03D11BA5" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> On the left hand side :
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Push the lever to unlock the take-up media shaft.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Slide the shaft out of the drive section to the outer position.
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-E584A50B-97E4-40EC-A97A-29402D77651A" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not remove the take-up media shaft yet. You may damage the drive / holder section.
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-00F899FB-B23C-4B66-A917-063034DE2096" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D23EDCA0-5117-48C5-BD7F-47AF0E97B224-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D23EDCA0-5117-48C5-BD7F-47AF0E97B224-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-E4D4ABD7-AE32-4366-86CC-66882340F09C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D7979B64-07E8-4215-83CD-4A7725D6BDDE-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D7979B64-07E8-4215-83CD-4A7725D6BDDE-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-3F02506A-9B5D-448B-B24A-1D3C3909E05A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5A189D56-A9FF-4CD8-BEA0-76EF05E37B4D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5A189D56-A9FF-4CD8-BEA0-76EF05E37B4D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Repeat this procedure on the right hand side.
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-E0B7BC91-2F71-412A-94FA-2225636DAEAA" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2819A711-120B-4E8B-9332-FA99ACAF4BC2-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2819A711-120B-4E8B-9332-FA99ACAF4BC2-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> lift and remove the take-up media shaft
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-F64B16D6-7C1E-4ECB-9046-DAB52790BF9F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2F9C8379-6D32-440A-9A0D-A69A6043427B-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2F9C8379-6D32-440A-9A0D-A69A6043427B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_944D21C7443944D5B66AB958B2ECB416" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
